comment: Official NSW Department of Education school code.
Commonwealth issued school location ID.
Official school name.
School street address (may include building/street number).
School suburb/town.
School postcode.
School phone
School email
School website
School fax
Full-time equivalent (FTE) student enrolments as reported under the Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) National Schools Collection (NSSC).

The percentage of full-time equivalent (FTE) students enrolled, as reported under the NSSC, who identify as Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islanders and are accepted in the community with which they associate.

The percentage of students (headcount) who are from language backgrounds other than English (LBOTE). A student is considered LBOTE if in their home a language other than English is spoken by the students, parents or guardians.

Index of Community Socio-Educational Advantage (ICSEA), sourced from ACARA. The ICSEA is a scale that represents levels of educational advantage. ICSEA values are on a scale, which has a mean of 1000 and a standard deviation of 100. ICSEA values range from around 500 (representing extremely disadvantaged backgrounds) to about 1300 (representing schools with students from very advantaged backgrounds).
Schooling level (or school type) flag. Options include: primary school, secondary school, central/community school.
Secondary school selective flag. Options include: fully selective, partially selective, not selective.
Opportunity class flag. (Y) or (N) a schoool offers opportunity classes for highly achieving Year 5 and 6 academically gifted students.
School speciality flag. Most NSW public schools are comprehensive, however, some schools offer a specialty as well. Options include: technology, sports, language, and creative and performing arts.

Further breakdown of a school level/type. Useful for differentiating junior secondary and senior secondary from standard 7-12 secondary schools. Also indicates the type of support provided in Schools for Specific Purposes.
Currently not available.
Preschool flag. (Y) or (N) a preschool is attached to the school.
Distance education flag. Options include: (s) distance education school, (c) distance education centre, (n) no distance education.
Intensive English flag. (Y) or (N) an intensive English centre is attached to this school
School population gender status. Options include: co-ed schools, girls schools, boys schools.
School late opening hours flag. (Y) or (N) a school opens later.
First teacher on duty date. Essentially, the official data of the school opened.
Local government area.
New South Wales electoral district (2015 boundaries).
Federal electorate divisions (2016 boundaries).
NSW Department of Education operational directorate.
NSW Department of Education principal network.

Family and Community Services district.
NSW local health districts. Eight local health districts cover the Sydney metropolitan region, and seven cover rural and regional NSW.
Aboriginal Education Consultative Group region.

Remoteness category based on the ABS' Australian Statistical Geography Standard (ASGS) 2016 remoteness structure. Options include: Major Cities, Inner Regional, Outer Regional, Remote and Very Remote.
School latitude coordinates.
School longitude coordinates.
The department's asset management districts across NSW.
